  <datafield tag="545" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">A race desegregation assistance center based at the University of Michigan, the Program for Educational Opportunity was established by funding through the 1964 Civil Rights Act.</subfield>
    <subfield code="b">The program was expanded to encompass race, gender, and national origin equity in public schools in the Great Lakes region.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Administrative files, topical files, workshop and task force material, handbooks, and material pertaining to desegregation and equality in public schools in Ann Arbor, Detroit, and elsewhere in Michigan and the Great Lakes region. Includes reports from school districts and histories of desegregation.</subfield>
